codex
The exact browser command is already a tight, deterministic red loop: both runs log successful portal login and `/auth/me`, then fail because the helper waits for a dashboard heading after the borrower receives the expected 403 from the staff dashboard endpoint.

Ranked hypotheses, which I’ll test without blocking:

1. The E2E login helper incorrectly treats a staff-dashboard heading as the proof of portal authentication. If so, waiting on a portal-authenticated route/session signal and navigating directly to MP07/MP11 will pass without changing permissions.
2. The fixture omitted a legitimate portal dashboard permission. If so, the seed’s intended role matrix would show that permission and granting it would make the existing heading appear.
3. The fixture’s member display name differs from the hard-coded heading. If so, the page renders a level-2 heading with different text while the session remains valid.
4. Login state is persisted too late for the first post-login navigation. If so, an explicit session/URL wait will eliminate the failure even with the same route.

I’m recording this repair plan now; the diagnosing skill’s feedback-loop discipline is keeping the fix scoped to the demonstrated browser failure rather than revisiting the green production implementation.
